    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-08T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-08T17:00:00-05:00" n="392"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">365D.1163/8: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-08T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 8, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>398. Your 670, December 6, 8 p.m. Please avoid taking any position that will
                    raise question as to the status or recognition of Italian Government in
                    Ethiopia. Your effort should be confined to having American interests given
                    ample opportunity to present evidence of value of property requisitioned and
                    prevent any unreasonable delay in payment of amount of compensation determined.
                    You will know whether appeal will be allowed from Commission finding should it
                    be unsatisfactory.</p>
                <p>Information is now being sought from the Sudan Interior Mission, and since its
                    headquarters are in Canada, there is possibility that American interests are not
                    predominant. Will inform you as to this.</p>
                <p>Do you consider that any useful purpose would be served by our endeavoring to
                    obtain postponement of requisition proceedings through the Embassy at Rome?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
